[u'Deletes a pool from the specified account.  When you request that a pool be deleted
column11: the following actions occur: the pool state is set to deleting
column12: any ongoing resize operation on the pool are stopped
column13: the Batch service starts resizing the pool to zero nodes
column14: any tasks running on existing nodes are terminated and requeued (as if a resize pool operation had been requested with the default requeue option)
column16: the pool is removed from the system. Because running tasks are requeued
column17: the user can rerun these tasks by updating their job to target a different pool. The tasks can then run on the new pool. If you want to override the requeue behavior
column18: then you should call resize pool explicitly to shrink the pool to zero size before deleting the pool. If you call an Update
column19: Patch or Delete API on a pool in the deleting state
column20: it will fail with HTTP status code 409 with error code PoolBeingDeleted.']
